01/06/2025,748.2855(a)(12) - Emergency Behavior Intervention,Emergency Behavior Intervention,No,01/13/2025,01/13/2025,N:Emergency Behavior Intervention,Medium,Yes,A restraint report dated 12.05.2024 doesn't include information regarding the child's return to normal activities.  This section was blank during the inspection. ,"The operation provided the following corrective action on January 13, 2025:
1.	Online Forms Implementation:
o	All restraint and EBI documentation forms have been moved online to ensure more efficient and standardized documentation.
o	The online forms now include a required section that specifically asks for information regarding the youths return to normal activities after a restraint, which will be filled out by staff. (See Attached)
2.	Staff Retraining:
o	We conducted retraining for staff on the importance of completing all sections of the EBI documentation, with a focus on the return-to-normal-activities section.
o	Staff were reminded that this section is critical and ensures that proper care is provided following a restraint.
o	Staff were also encouraged to type out the Serious Incident documentation instead of writing it out.
Attached Documents:
	Attached are the updated Serious Incident Reporting form and the new online EBI documentation system.
	Copies of agenda and sign in sheet provided to staff during the training session on January 9, 2025.
Compliance Timeline:
	All staff were retrained on restraint documentation. It was completed as of January 9th, 2025. See attached for agenda and sign in sheet.
	The online system for EBI documentation is now fully operational, and all relevant forms are being completed according to the updated protocol.
	Ongoing staff education and audits of documentation will occur monthly to ensure continued compliance.
