01/06/2025,748.313(4) - Individual Standards Evaluated,Individual Standards Evaluated,No,01/13/2025,01/13/2025,Individual Standards Evaluated,Medium,Yes,"Serious incident report dated 01/02/2025 is marked as ""yes"" or ""no"", but the report doesn't document the differences, and more than one child was involved based on the report.","The operation provided the following response on January 13, 2025:
1.	Staff Training:
o	A general staff training session was conducted to educate all staff on the proper procedure for filling out Serious Incident Reports on 1/9/2025. (see attached for sign in sheet and Agena)
o	Emphasis was placed on the necessity of documenting differences in size, age, and developmental levels of children involved in serious incidents, as well as providing clear descriptions for each involved child.
o	The training also covered the importance of accurately following the report instructions, particularly regarding the de-identification of other youth involved by using their initials.  
2.	Implementation of New Reporting Protocol:
o	Staff were trained on 1/9/2025  to ensure that all Serious Incident Reports are completed in compliance with the requirements. This includes more thorough documentation of any incidents involving multiple children, with careful attention to their size, age, and developmental levels.
o	Supervisors will be required to review each Serious Incident Report for completeness and accuracy before submission
"
07/22/2024,748.751(a)(1) - Personnel,Personnel,No,08/05/2024,07/23/2024,E:Personnel,Medium,Yes,Employee files only included one place of employment.,"Operation provided the following compliance plan:
1.Policy Update: Revise the pre-employment screening policy to emphasize the requirement of obtaining a written employment history for the last five years from each applicant before hiring.
2. Form Integration: Add the pre-employment screening form, including the reference check form, to the employee application packet to ensure it is completed during the hiring process.
3. Procedure Enhancement: Use the pre-employment screening form so that applicants must complete during their onboarding, detailing their employment for the past five years.
4. Training: Train staff involved in hiring effective reference-checking techniques and the importance of thorough verification.
5. Record Keeping: Ensure that completed reference check forms are included in the applicant's file as part of the mandatory documentation.
6. Audit and Compliance: Implement a quarterly audit process to review a random sample of hiring files to verify compliance with the employment history requirement."
07/22/2024,748.753(a)(2) - Personnel,Personnel,No,08/05/2024,07/23/2024,E:Personnel,Medium High,Yes,Employee files did not include documentation of reference checks.,"Operation provided the following compliance plan:
Corrective Actions:
1. Policy Update: Revise the pre-employment screening policy to emphasize the requirement of contacting at least two references for each applicant.
2. Procedure Enhancement: Develop a standardized reference check form to document the feedback received from
each reference contact.
3. Form Integration: Add the pre-employment screening form, including the reference check form, to the employee application packet to ensure it is completed during the hiring process.
4. Training: Train staff involved in hiring effective reference-checking techniques and the importance of thorough verification.
5. Record Keeping:
Ensure that completed reference check forms are included in the applicant's file as part of the mandatory documentation.
6. Audit and Compliance:
Implement a quarterly audit process to review a random sample of hiring files to verify compliance with the reference-checking requirement."
